Rating: 4
This recipe is nothing short of astounding! On short notice I found myself hosting Christmas dinner (my friends' cat died and they couldn't deal with entertaining...) so I decided to cook kwanzaa food and found this recipe on epicurious and served it to the general ravishment of all. I'll make it many times in the future. I served it with the accompanying epicurious recipes for collard greens, sweet potato souffle and peach cobbler and "The Joy of Cooking" hominy casserole. The guests went through this stuff like a swarm of locusts. One guest from the South raved about the authenticity of the finished products. Big thumbs up!

