Rating: 4
I'm not really supposed to rate this because I left out the vinegar and ginger (the latter was an accident). But it was GREAT. Marinated for 24 hours, so the chicken was very tender and with balanced sour/sweet, spicy/perfumy results. Simply baked in oven 375-400 degrees until skin was brown and crispy. Chicken didn't dry out. We ate it with collards and sweet potato puree.

Rating: 4
I love Al Roker's Jerk Chicken recipe, but I believe this may be better. I made one third of the marinade for 2 large breasts and 4 small thighs. I substituted half a jalapeno with seeds for the Scotch bonnet and accidentally omitted the lime juice. The result was fantastic. The spice blend and degree of heat are perfect for my taste. I marinaded the chicken only a couple of hours, yet the fabulous taste permeated the chicken. This is definite keeper.

Rating: 1
I love jerk chicken but this version I found to be too heavy on the lime flavor. I used fresh lime juice and marinated it for 6 hours. I followed this recipe precisely except I used jalapeno pepper. It was OK, just not great. I served it with red rice and fresh mango on the side. I wish I could find the other jerk recipe I used to use. I think it had soy sauce (!) in it.

Rating: 1
