Rating: 4
This recipe uses high doses of the spices making the meat intensely flavorful and the whole house smell wonderful...a real treat for arriving guests. I would recommend a few variations. I prefer a bit more hot chilis. You can spice this up a bit without endangering the quality of the dish. I much prefer using dark brown sugar, instead of white, and more of it.

Rating: 3
I made this for a group of 7 after returning from the Caribbean for my honeymoon. I wanted to make an authentic Caribbean dish and it was a huge hit! I made it in the oven and broiled it for a few minutes at the end to make the skin crispy. I also doubled the recipe and felt it had a bit too much lime flavor. The flavor of the marinade is really unique and I will definitely make this again.

